Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.87,0:00:04.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't taken a shower recently, \N have you, Mr. Mauler?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.91,0:00:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought we agreed when you moved \N to the desk next to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.00,0:00:10.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that you would at least take a shower every two days!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.96,0:00:12.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God, you are so annoying!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.59,0:00:15.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is a guest in the reception room.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.76,0:00:20.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going home now, so please make \N some tea for him yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.09,0:00:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A guest?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.05,0:00:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.76,0:00:25.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has not taken a bath in while, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.14,0:00:27.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He smells as bad as you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.18,0:00:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that supposed to mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.98,0:00:37.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whose fault is it that I haven't taken a bath in a while?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.90,0:00:43.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only reason you can still work for this newspaper \N with no hope for advancement...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.83,0:00:46.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is all thanks to the great Mauler.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.39,0:00:48.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet she doesn't even realize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.46,0:00:49.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.37,0:00:52.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to keep you waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.63,0:00:55.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.42,0:00:58.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, I hope you can help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.88,0:01:00.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.55,0:01:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is indeed dirty.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.76,0:01:07.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.  So you are a doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.39,0:01:09.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure don't look like one, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.77,0:01:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Doctor, is this what you are trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.61,0:01:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The next target in the slew of middle aged couple \N murders happening throughout Germany...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.32,0:01:21.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is here in Heidelberg.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.95,0:01:24.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That a middle aged couple has a foster daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.20,0:01:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When she turns twenty, the killer \N will come to take her away.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.20,0:01:32.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when that happens, the foster \N parents will definitely be killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.17,0:01:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you don't know who or where the \N foster parents and the girl are.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.22,0:01:47.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have got some sort of complex!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.93,0:01:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is no laughing matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.35,0:01:50.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please believe me!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.73,0:01:51.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is just nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.06,0:01:55.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not even a third rate tabloid would buy a story like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.92,0:01:57.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't come to here so you could write an article about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.48,0:02:00.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is more than a six month gap...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.90,0:02:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...between the time the twins disappeared \N from the hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.70,0:02:04.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and when the brother reappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.07,0:02:06.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.57,0:02:12.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to my theory, they came here to Heidelberg \N after they disappeared from the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.83,0:02:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, according to your theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.25,0:02:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the two were raised by the current \N foster parents of the sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.00,0:02:22.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the brother ran away shortly after coming here...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.17,0:02:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...leaving the sister behind with the parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.01,0:02:27.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should write a book about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.01,0:02:29.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although I doubt it would sell very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.06,0:02:32.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is a chance that a search request \N was filed for the brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.35,0:02:35.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it might have appeared in a newspaper!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.44,0:02:39.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please allow me to look through the \N newspapers from nine years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.82,0:02:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm begging you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.32,0:02:46.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.87,0:02:50.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There must not be any more victims!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.37,0:02:52.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please...!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.97,0:03:07.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The boss is allergic to hiring help.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.14,0:03:12.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here are the compact editions and files \N of the manuscripts from that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.60,0:03:17.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And these are the rough drafts \N and files of the material used.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.27,0:03:20.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.19,0:03:24.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is what they call a Japanese bow?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.19,0:03:25.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are very welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.40,0:03:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the record, I just didn't want to listen \N to your stupid stories anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.33,0:03:34.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just hurry up and go home when you are done.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.62,0:03:41.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, we get those kinds of weirdos sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.30,0:03:46.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.26,0:03:50.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please let it be here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.04,0:05:23.76,Stuff,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(350,332)}The Missing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.37,0:05:24.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.20,0:05:26.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.41,0:05:27.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm so glad!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.60,0:05:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You seem fine, Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.16,0:05:32.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You scared us to death when you fainted so suddenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.13,0:05:35.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you really didn't like the \N man we introduced to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.50,0:05:37.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, that's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.59,0:05:39.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just suddenly felt sick, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.88,0:05:41.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should apologize to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.34,0:05:42.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh that's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.34,0:05:44.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to worry about that guy anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.64,0:05:51.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After talking to some people, it turned out that \N Otto guy wasn't your prince on a white horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.02,0:05:54.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he didn't email anything like that to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.69,0:05:57.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.74,0:06:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are saying that the reason you fainted \N was because you saw that man?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.49,0:06:07.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.79,0:06:09.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was he like?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.91,0:06:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I only saw him for a split second, \N so I don't really remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.58,0:06:15.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.42,0:06:17.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of impression did you get from him?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.76,0:06:19.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Somewhat nostalgic...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.30,0:06:24.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that is not exactly it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.62,0:06:26.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't quite explain it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.26,0:06:28.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.41,0:06:47.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is okay, Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.53,0:06:48.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You do not have to push yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.08,0:06:50.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Absolute evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.66,0:06:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't quite explain it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.46,0:06:58.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I felt the same thing as when I had those nightmares.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.71,0:07:04.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we are talking about absolute evil, \N then we are talking about religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.76,0:07:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't attend church either, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.43,0:07:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think if I see him again, I'll understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.81,0:07:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You feel that your lost memories will come back?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.44,0:07:18.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.73,0:07:20.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is one method.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.78,0:07:25.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't think you need to set that as a goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.57,0:07:28.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's also important to think of the future \N without pushing yourself to the limits.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.16,0:07:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.37,0:07:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything is okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.62,0:07:36.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go play some sports, sweat it out, and your anxiety will be gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.01,0:07:45.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You pulled an all nighter again, Mr. Mauler?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.80,0:07:47.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.12,0:07:48.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.18,0:07:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you the one who let that man use the reference room?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.27,0:07:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That man?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.52,0:07:55.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.52,0:07:59.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was there just now, so I asked him, \N and he said he had your permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.02,0:08:01.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is still here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.73,0:08:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.49,0:08:08.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!  You should...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.75,0:08:13.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.58,0:08:15.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.83,0:08:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.80,0:08:28.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead.  Eat up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.93,0:08:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.35,0:08:39.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is good, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.44,0:08:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I always come to this restaurant for breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.27,0:08:44.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't go home?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.61,0:08:45.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a family?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.69,0:08:47.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.13,0:08:49.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My wife left me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.37,0:08:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was too busy with work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.08,0:08:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I finally realized it, my wife had taken my \N daughter and went back to her home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.54,0:09:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you want to go and get your wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.55,0:09:04.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.71,0:09:06.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She is the one who left.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.55,0:09:08.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why should I go and pick her up?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.97,0:09:13.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you seem to regret being so \N occupied with your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.43,0:09:15.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop all that nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.81,0:09:18.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A man's first priority is his job.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.31,0:09:22.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, if she leaves because she can't understand \N this line of work, then so be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.69,0:09:24.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for saying such things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.03,0:09:27.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's none of your business.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.57,0:09:30.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.64,0:09:32.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are smoking too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.55,0:09:34.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm warning you as a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.16,0:09:36.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said it is none of your business!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.54,0:09:38.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop talking like my wife!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.25,0:09:42.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means your wife was worried about your health.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.80,0:09:50.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's none of your business.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.85,0:09:54.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that a birthday present for Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.39,0:09:57.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I finally finshed knitting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.73,0:10:01.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She used to wear sweaters this small when she was little.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.77,0:10:05.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dear, are you really going to tell her?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.57,0:10:09.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That she isn't our biological daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.15,0:10:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind things the way they are right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.07,0:10:15.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you are right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.74,0:10:17.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have to tell her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.29,0:10:21.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina is our daughter, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.42,0:10:24.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm home!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.84,0:10:26.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.21,0:10:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm so hungry!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.22,0:10:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think about my future, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.43,0:10:38.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe Dr. Geitel's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.74,0:11:01.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Tomorrow at 7 pm, on the night of your birthday, \N we will meet at Heidelberg Castle."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.96,0:11:04.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.67,0:11:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At Heidelberg Castle...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.38,0:11:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe I'm starting at a pile of scraps with \N you when I have so much of my own work to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.80,0:11:19.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't you give up already?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.65,0:11:30.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Doctor....
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.86,0:11:33.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If, and I'm just saying if...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.90,0:11:38.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I, uh went to see my wife...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.24,0:11:39.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think she would come back with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.08,0:11:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, if you stop smoking.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.42,0:11:50.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.46,0:11:52.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.38,0:11:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"An eleven year old boy missing..."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.64,0:11:58.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"There is a possibility of abduction..."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.47,0:12:02.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"...but there have been no ransom requests or \N messages from the kidnappers at this point."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.39,0:12:04.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Number 16, Neckar Street."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.94,0:12:07.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone named Fortner requested a search!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.23,0:12:12.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There should be more information \N about that article in here...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.74,0:12:13.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.78,0:12:20.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.87,0:12:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said the killer was going to pick up his \N sister when she turned twenty, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.83,0:12:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the boy in this article is her brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.54,0:12:33.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, his birth date is written here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.05,0:12:38.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today is the twins' twentieth birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.87,0:12:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Papa.  It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.77,0:12:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just got off work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.21,0:12:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to meet up with a friend now, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.17,0:12:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, at Heidelberg Castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.25,0:13:00.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.  Your mom is preparing a birthday \N party for you right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.18,0:13:04.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was that Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.60,0:13:07.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, she said she'll be back after seeing a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.72,0:13:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what kind of friend he is?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.56,0:13:12.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina's about that age now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.23,0:13:15.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe now I can finally understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.65,0:13:18.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...my memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.07,0:13:26.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to know who I really am...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.58,0:13:31.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Doctor, what are you going to do if the \N twin sister really was at the Fortner's?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.58,0:13:35.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, the family is definitely in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.54,0:13:38.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll call the police and ask them to guard the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.71,0:13:42.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think the police will take action \N just because of your theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.05,0:13:44.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing has even happened yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.39,0:13:46.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too late to call for help after something has happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.35,0:13:48.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing will happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.31,0:13:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is all in your imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.77,0:13:53.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to me, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.81,0:13:56.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of the four murder cases...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.65,0:13:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I went to the Köln crime scene to ask some questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.32,0:14:02.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That crime was special.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.15,0:14:05.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't see any purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.11,0:14:08.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't sense any purpose or hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.49,0:14:12.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It felt like the point was just to end their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.66,0:14:15.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you see a crime scene like that, \N you'll immediately understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.88,0:14:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said a boy not even twenty was the killer, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.00,0:14:24.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...do you really think a child like that \N can kill without any emotion?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.76,0:14:27.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was not a child's doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.30,0:14:29.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was something bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.31,0:14:32.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by "something bigger"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.10,0:14:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.85,0:14:37.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't find the right words for this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.99,0:14:47.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I had to say something, it would sound like a cop out, but....
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.24,0:14:49.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that was the work of the devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.49,0:14:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the killer appeared in front of me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.46,0:14:56.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I'd kill him without any hesitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.13,0:15:06.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Number 16, Neckar Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.38,0:15:07.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.60,0:15:14.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good evening!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.68,0:15:16.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to intrude on you so late!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.65,0:15:21.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.20,0:15:30.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.  I'm Mauler from the Heidelberg Post.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.80,0:15:32.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does a newspaper reporter want with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.08,0:15:36.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to ask you about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.75,0:15:40.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.67,0:15:41.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.59,0:15:48.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...it's about the search request that \N you filed for a boy in 1986.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.05,0:15:53.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-We don't want to talk about that anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.81,0:15:57.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, can I ask you some questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.27,0:15:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.40,0:16:02.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The twin sister of the brother that went missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.86,0:16:06.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.07,0:16:10.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.87,0:16:12.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cake.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.45,0:16:16.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was preparing the cake for the birthday party.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.79,0:16:21.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You took in the twins nine years ago, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.54,0:16:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sister lives here, doesn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.13,0:16:25.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please go away!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.30,0:16:31.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We raised Nina as our real daughter until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.39,0:16:33.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, don't cause any problems for us!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.47,0:16:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave us alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.64,0:16:38.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You took the twins in nine years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.35,0:16:40.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The brother had a scar on his head from surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.48,0:16:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the sister had amnesia.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.31,0:16:43.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.90,0:16:50.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Fortner!  We have to call the police immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.70,0:16:53.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You and your daughter's lives are in danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.53,0:16:55.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Mauler...?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.21,0:17:03.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.21,0:17:06.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please let us speak with your daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.55,0:17:08.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She is out right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.63,0:17:10.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.59,0:17:13.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She is at Heidelberg Castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.39,0:17:15.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She said something about meeting a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.27,0:17:18.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me use your car!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.68,0:17:21.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, we have to call the police first!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.77,0:17:25.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have time to give the \N police a thorough explanation!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.11,0:17:25.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry and give me the keys!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.90,0:17:30.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright.  I'll call the police from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.45,0:17:32.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.53,0:17:34.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.70,0:17:37.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.99,0:17:40.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I just said, the boy is messed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.75,0:17:42.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you dare die!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.37,0:17:44.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Mauler...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.04,0:17:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come back alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.17,0:17:48.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you do...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.38,0:17:51.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I'll stop smoking, just like you suggested, you quack.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.47,0:17:54.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You wife will be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.05,0:18:00.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, how am I supposed \N to explain this to the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.22,0:18:03.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is our daughter safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.33,0:18:05.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.40,0:18:06.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.86,0:18:07.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me borrow your phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.82,0:18:10.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen to our daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.65,0:18:12.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please tell us!  Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.99,0:18:14.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.45,0:18:22.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could this happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.66,0:18:26.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The phone line has been cut!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.18,0:18:40.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.47,0:18:42.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please be safe, Anna!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.94,0:18:48.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is way past the time we were supposed to meet...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.98,0:18:51.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it was a prank after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.78,0:18:53.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I'll go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.74,0:18:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.21,0:19:12.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have to wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.93,0:19:20.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.18,0:19:24.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He asked me...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.43,0:19:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...to make sure you would wait for him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.44,0:19:35.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said wait.  Don't you understand what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.82,0:19:39.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.87,0:19:42.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have to wait here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.12,0:19:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He told me so!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.37,0:19:46.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.30,0:19:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.67,0:19:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you are Nina Fortner, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.13,0:19:59.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.36,0:20:00.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Doctor Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.85,0:20:02.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank God you are safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.51,0:20:04.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.81,0:20:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.31,0:20:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let's go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.60,0:20:12.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are the prince on the white horse?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.90,0:20:15.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.49,0:20:18.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't interefere...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.26,0:20:19.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't interfere!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.62,0:20:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She has to wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.66,0:20:26.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.77,0:20:27.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.66,0:20:31.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't get my money!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.59,0:20:35.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said no one would come!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.46,0:20:38.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.19,0:20:52.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.82,0:20:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That surprised me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.07,0:20:57.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me something to tie his hands with!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.66,0:21:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who hired you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.24,0:21:06.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.29,0:21:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When did he say he was coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.45,0:21:09.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.62,0:21:13.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He only said that he'll come here after he has \N taken care of something important!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.67,0:21:17.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.00,0:21:18.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your house!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.88,0:21:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to hurry back to your house!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.51,0:21:24.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.35,0:21:26.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll explain later!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.79,0:21:27.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry, Anna!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.56,0:21:29.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.37,0:21:29.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.52,0:21:38.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!  I can't get loose!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.09,0:21:57.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.46,0:22:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.69,0:22:02.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And my name is not Anna.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.80,0:22:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.74,0:22:04.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.89,0:22:09.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you were brought into my \N hospital, your name was Anna.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.18,0:22:09.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.39,0:22:12.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...your brother's name...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.06,0:22:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.94,0:22:17.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother?
